commit.message:
Switch default testing to RHEL from CentOS

Some places, the CentOS image is still referenced because for those
specific tests, it's better to use a non-default image.  Also, in most
places, updated the CentOS tag from 7 -> latest.  Mainly for cosmetic
purposes, though it does squah any confusion that perhaps the 7-GA
version was being used.

Signed-off-by: Chris Evich <cevich@redhat.com>

Remove run-from atomic feature.

Largely replaced by ADEPT:
https://github.com/cevich/autotest-docker-enabled-product-testing

Signed-off-by: Chris Evich <cevich@redhat.com>

Atomic: Simplify use on atomic to bare minumum

Signed-off-by: Chris Evich <cevich@redhat.com>

Centralize Image/Container preservation & cleanup

* Fix Atomic host scripts and config. to better preserve images/containers.

* Fix Atomic host generated config. to be valid/proper.

* Unify image & container cleanup from iterables in ``clean_all()``
  methods.  Add basic unittests.

* Move ``ignore_*`` options from intratests.ini into globals for access
  by ``clean_all()`` during testing.

* Clean up garbage_check intratest code, to use new global options.

* Update most subtests and sub-subtests to use ``clean_all()``

* Fix some faulty code in a handful of tests.

Signed-off-by: Chris Evich <cevich@redhat.com>

Atomic: Switch back to building from repo

This makes it easier to have bundled custom
configuration and tests.

Signed-off-by: Chris Evich <cevich@redhat.com>

Atomic: Make build/install easier + modular

Previously everything was jammed into a single Dockerfile,
but a handful of scripts are also included.  Since the command
line for 'atomic install' is encoded in the Dockerfile,
it's more flexible to just call a script to finish the build.
This allows for more flexibility in base-image, install options,
and source locations.

Signed-off-by: Chris Evich <root@atomichost.local>

Atomic: Exclude unsafe/broken/failing tests

Signed-off-by: Chris Evich <cevich@redhat.com>

Atomic: Fix container access to /run and /var/log

When running under atomic, the docker_autotest container needs access to the docker socket and host logs

Support running under project Atomic's atomic cmd

Signed-off-by: Chris Evich <cevich@redhat.com>

Dockerfile: Support building/testing in Docker SPC

SPC: Super Provileged Container

Signed-off-by: Chris Evich <cevich@redhat.com>

docker_cli/build: Fix cleanup() removing base images

Also added a .dockerignore and updated Dockerfile to actually change
some layer content during builds.

Signed-off-by: Chris Evich <cevich@redhat.com>
